headline: US refiners struggle to absorb sudden surge in Venezuelan oil imports
summary: HOUSTON/NEW YORK, Feb 3 (Reuters) - Oil refiners on the U. Gulf Coast are struggling to absorb a rapid surge in Venezuelan crude shipments since last month's flagship $2 billion supply deal between Caracas and Washington, pressuring prices and leaving some volumes unsold, according to traders and shipping data.
